\fs46 \cf0 1 Introduction
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\fs32 \cf0 As e-commerce enjoys a boom and lots people are using those services such Amazon, Ebay and so on, recommender systems becomes an important issue in the research area. Recommender systems recommend a personalized and ranked information or items to users based on users\'92 profiles, preferences and experiences. The recommender system compares the items and users\'92 infor- mation and find correlations among them and make recommendations. [1] presents an overview of the academic and industry research areas of recom- mender systems and analyses the advantages and limitations of the current recommendation methods in the following three fields: content-based, col- laborative, and hybrid recommend methods. [1] also discusses some possible extensions to improve the recommender systems\'92 capabilities.
\fs24 \

\fs32 Collaborative filtering is one of the most important and widely applied methods in recommender systems. Collaborative filtering recommend items to users based on the items\'92 scores rated by users and users\'92 historic prefer- ences. The common ways of collaborative filtering process is first group users with same preferences or \'92taste\'92 together and then find the similar items ac- cording to the ratings from the users in the same group. Finally the items that are most liked will be recommended to the users who have not rate this.
